spans.text: , Goddess , wilt thou never smile Indulgent on Britannia's isle
Amid shrouded friends who solemn stalk
Lament his dastard sons in vain
happier climes belong The painter's tints
Prepared to leave our desert land
Each speaking passion of the mind
consent the Muse's choir To thee shall dedicate the Lyre
the Muse's choir To thee shall dedicate the Lyre
Let me direct thy pleasing flight
the soft guardian of thy charms

Her tender social tears with thine , Over every urn fresh laurels strow , And fondly emulate thy woe
her barren sway , Where never the Muse's chaplet blew , Where Learning's laurel never grew

Each pleasing sound she sighs to
The mutual wishes of her soul
to her admiring youth Sweet tales of innocence and truth

Where fierce Atlantic surges roar : Where Plata with resistless force Through deserts rolls his rapid course , Or where Maranan proudly laves Waste regions with his circling waves : Where boundless Oroonoko fills His channels from a thousand hills , And with regardless rage destroys ; While twenty mouths with hideous noise , From some immense Peruvian steep , Spout his vexed billows to the deep

shalt all his toils repay , Slow-lingering here with fond delay
